	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=11453&mid=105437758196110>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=11453&mid=105437758196110>Mark of Sorcery</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=11453&mid=105437758196110#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, May 31st 7:22 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=135690><span id=Scholar>Fel</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>219 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.53]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Everyone's pretty much covered the details on this but just a quick note, the Mark of Sorcery is No Drop. So far it is the only No Drop piece I have seen for these quests but I haven't done them all. Just incase you have been looking in the bazaar for it, it won't appear, except maybe on FV.<br><br>Gladiator spawns to the right of the stairs to Bedlavar's building (Duelist also spawns there) and if you are close to the appropriate level for these quests you will want an aggro reducer on the others. I think you can start single pulling at 53, I am certain I was able to at 54, at least.<br>Pull him to the south towards Katte&nbsp;&nbsp;(before the steep incline) nothing else paths down there that I have seen.<br><br>Robe is a nice piece for the appropriate level (high 30's to mid 40's) but by the time you've finished one of the Chest piece quests you'll prolly be high 40's minimum (even if you spend all your time just doing the quest) and will then be capable of getting much better items. It does fill in as a stop gap and knowledge there is a purpose to all the killing helps with the level grind.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
